### Description

# Host Directive Input Binding Not Working with Router Data

## Description
When using `withComponentInputBinding()` with the Router, input bindings for host directives fail to receive values from route data, while component inputs work correctly.

## Reproduction

```typescript
@Directive()
export class HelloComponentStore {
  readonly hostDirectiveInputValue = input<string>('failed');
}

@Component({
  template: `
    <h2>componentInputValue: {{ componentInputValue() }}!</h2>
    <h2>hostDirectiveInputValue: {{ store.hostDirectiveInputValue() }}!</h2>
  `,
  hostDirectives: [
    {
      directive: HelloComponentStore,
      inputs: ['hostDirectiveInputValue']
    }
  ],
})
export class HelloComponent {
  readonly store = inject(HelloComponentStore);
  readonly componentInputValue = input<string>();
}

// Router configuration
bootstrapApplication(App, {
  providers: [
    provideRouter([
      { 
        path: '',
        component: HelloComponent,
        data: {
          componentInputValue: 'success',    // Works
          hostDirectiveInputValue: 'success' // Doesn't work - stays as 'failed'
        }
      }
    ], withComponentInputBinding()
    )
  ]
});
```

DEMO: https://stackblitz.com/edit/sb1-fact8gpx?file=src%2Fmain.ts


## Expected Behavior
Both componentInputValue and hostDirectiveInputValue should receive their values from the route data when using withComponentInputBinding().

## Actual Behavior
Component input (componentInputValue) correctly receives 'success' from route data
Host directive input (hostDirectiveInputValue) remains at its default value 'failed'

## Environment
Angular version: 19.0.6
TypeScript version: 5.6.3

## Additional Context
This appears to be a regression or oversight in the implementation of withComponentInputBinding(), as it doesn't properly handle input bindings for host directives.




